node.text: Capella satellites can peer right through cloud cover, and see just as well in the daylight as in total darkness. That’s because instead of optical imaging, it uses synthetic aperture radar, or SAR. 🛰🤯

node.text: The fact this 73-year-old Jeep is still driveable is mind-boggling 🤯

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by UNILAD Tech on August 22, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'UNILAD TECH Japan tests exploding. rocket engine for the first time in space'.

node.text: The rotary engine produced about 500 Newtons of thrust, only a fraction of what conventional rocket engines are capable of currently. However, with some upgrades, it could quickly surpass the traditional rocket 🚀

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by UNILAD Tech on August 21, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'UNILAD TECH oceanexploration exploration Electric exploration submarine wants to be SpaceX of the sea'.

node.text: Considering we know more about space than we do the ocean floor of our own planet, it's about time we went searching. 🤿

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by UNILAD Tech on August 20, 2021. May be an image of body of water and text that says 'UNILAD TECH Climate alert: Itrained on Greenland's ce sheet for the first time in recorded history'.

node.text: A torrential downpour containing 7 billion tonnes of rain washed away 337,000 square miles of the ice shelf. That's about half of it and is the second major ice melt in two weeks. 🌍👀

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by UNILAD Tech on August 20, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'News Elon Musk unveils a humanoid robot utilising Tesla's vehicle AI called Tesla Bot'.

node.text: Musk made sure he pointed out that you could both outrun the Tesla Bot and "overpower" it if needed 🤖🤯
